<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 18 at 9:26AM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...Snow Covered and Slick Roads This Morning...
The snow will slowly taper off to flurries and or light freezing
drizzle from west to east between 11 AM and 1 PM. Until then
additional accumulations of a half inch or less can be expected.
Locations in and around Southfield, Royal Oak, Warren and Mount
Clemens will continue to see more of a sleet and freezing rain
mix. Temperatures will hold mainly at or below freezing into early
afternoon. Untreated roads will remain snow covered and slick.
Drivers should continue to exercise caution this morning.</description>
